  <summary>9/21/1987--Introduced.
Amends employment tax provisions of the Internal Revenue Code to accord self-employed status to up to 30 qualifying fishermen on a boat. (Under current law, such status is granted only when a boat's operating crew normally consists of fewer than ten individuals.)</summary>
